The police service on Wednesday unveiled a gymnasium for its officers at the Presidential Escort unit in Ruiru camp. The facility was officially commissioned by Inspector General of Police Joseph Boinnet. The modern training facility has been equipped with a variety of exercise and fitness equipment. “The equipment installed at the Presidential Escort Unit Ruiru Camp was donated by the LOTTO Foundation and will be used by Police Officers to exercise and keep fit,” the National Police Service said in a tweet.  Click here for the latest political news  